soc.message
Class PlayerElements

java.lang.Object
  soc.message.Message
      soc.message.MessageMulti
          soc.message.MessageTemplateMi
              soc.message.PlayerElements
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class PlayerElements
extends MessageTemplateMi

This message from the server holds information on some parts of the player's status, such as resource type counts. Same structure as PlayerElement but with less redundancy when sending multiple messages. For a given player number and action type, contains multiple pairs of (element type, value).

Since:
1.1.09
Author:
Jeremy D Monin

Constructor Detail

PlayerElements

public PlayerElements(java.lang.String ga,
                      int pn,
                      int ac,
                      int[] et,
                      int[] va)
               throws java.lang.NullPointerException
Constructor for server to tell client about player elements.

Parameters:
ga - name of the game
pn - the player number
ac - the type of action: PlayerElement.SET, PlayerElement.GAIN, or PlayerElement.LOSE
et - array of the types of element, such as PlayerElement.SETTLEMENTS
va - array of the values of each element, corresponding to et[]
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if et null or va null

parseDataStr

public static PlayerElements parseDataStr(java.lang.String[] pa)
Parse the command String array into a PlayerElements message.

Parameters:
pa - the parameters; length 5 or more required. Length must be odd.
 pa[0] = playerNum
 pa[1] = actionType
 pa[2] = elementType[0]
 pa[3] = value[0]
 pa[4] = elementType[1]
 pa[5] = value[1]
(etc.)
Returns:
a PlayerElements message, or null if parsing errors
